1
00:00:12,358 --> 00:00:15,319
Many strange tales
are told of this jungle.

2
00:00:15,680 --> 00:00:20,189
But none so strange as the
tale of the cub we call Mowgli.

3
00:01:33,301 --> 00:01:35,975
You must be the very
worst wolf I've ever seen.

4
00:01:36,436 --> 00:01:38,726
Yeah, but if the branch
didn't break, I would've made it.

5
00:01:39,644 --> 00:01:43,606
Crossing upwind, breaking from your numbers.
If you can't learn to run with the pack...

6
00:01:43,814 --> 00:01:45,673
One of these days,
you'll be someone's dinner.

7
00:01:45,805 --> 00:01:46,035
How'd we do?

8
00:01:46,132 --> 00:01:47,204
Got Mowgli again!

9
00:01:47,336 --> 00:01:49,292
- He's never gonna make the council.
- Let's go!

10
00:01:51,947 --> 00:01:53,406
It was higher ground.

11
00:01:53,782 --> 00:01:55,992
Wolves don't hide in trees.

12
00:01:56,284 --> 00:01:59,564
I can't keep up with them, Bagheera.
I tried. I just picked the wrong tree.

13
00:01:59,704 --> 00:02:00,788
It was a dead tree.

14
00:02:01,080 --> 00:02:03,249
How was I supposed
to know it was dead?

15
00:02:03,624 --> 00:02:06,627
It had a fig vine. Any
tree girdled by a creeper...

16
00:02:06,960 --> 00:02:10,589
Is either dead or close to it.
These are things a wolf must know.

17
00:02:11,506 --> 00:02:14,509
Yeah, but if the branch
didn't break, I would've made it.

18
00:02:15,927 --> 00:02:17,720
I realize you weren't
born a wolf, but...

19
00:02:18,054 --> 00:02:20,097
Couldn't you at least act like one?

20
00:02:24,268 --> 00:02:27,729
When I found him,
many years ago...

21
00:02:28,397 --> 00:02:31,483
He was just an infant,
abandoned in the woods.

22
00:02:31,861 --> 00:02:32,889
Get the deer!

23
00:02:34,319 --> 00:02:39,323
If he was going to survive,
I knew he needed a people.

24
00:02:39,615 --> 00:02:41,617
A people to protect him.

25
00:02:42,284 --> 00:02:44,745
It's why I entrusted
him to the wolves.

26
00:02:51,585 --> 00:02:57,298
Akela, was a just and noble leader,
he allowed Mowgli to dwell among them.

27
00:02:57,632 --> 00:02:59,258
All those years.

28
00:03:01,302 --> 00:03:06,140
But, trouble was, wolves
grew so fast and Mowgli, well...

29
00:03:06,390 --> 00:03:09,309
Let's just say he
liked to take his time.

30
00:03:09,518 --> 00:03:12,187
- Mowgli, take me up high!
- Stop, not now.

31
00:03:13,313 --> 00:03:17,442
It was Raksha who raised him.
She was the only mother he ever knew.

32
00:03:17,733 --> 00:03:20,403
- Come on, let's play.
- I don't feel like playing, Gray.

33
00:03:20,778 --> 00:03:22,947
Come on, you're my brother.
You have to play with me.

34
00:03:23,197 --> 00:03:24,490
Let's go chase some mice!

35
00:03:27,075 --> 00:03:28,744
How did it go?

36
00:03:29,411 --> 00:03:30,954
Caught me again.

37
00:03:31,913 --> 00:03:34,916
If it's meant
to be, it will be.

38
00:03:36,250 --> 00:03:38,285
Let me hear the law.

39
00:03:38,978 --> 00:03:40,809
This is the law of the jungle.

40
00:03:40,961 --> 00:03:43,280
As old and as true as the sky.

41
00:03:43,396 --> 00:03:45,985
The wolf that keeps it will prosper...

42
00:03:46,368 --> 00:03:48,650
The wolf that breaks it will die.

43
00:03:48,997 --> 00:03:51,477
Like the creeper that
girdles the tree trunk...

44
00:03:51,677 --> 00:03:53,752
The law runneth over and back.

45
00:03:54,017 --> 00:03:56,477
For the strength of
the pack is the wolf...

46
00:03:56,769 --> 00:03:59,581
And the strength of
the wolf is the pack.

47
00:04:28,715 --> 00:04:32,135
Soon, the rains ceased to
fall and the dry season arrived.

48
00:04:38,287 --> 00:04:39,892
Heat crept through the jungle.

49
00:04:40,184 --> 00:04:44,146
Turning it yellow,
then brown, then black.

50
00:04:47,160 --> 00:04:51,975
But that year was the driest
season that anyone can remember.

51
00:04:52,153 --> 00:04:53,732
Even the moab didn't flower.

52
00:04:59,493 --> 00:05:00,619
My leaf.

53
00:05:02,246 --> 00:05:04,456
This is mine, mine, mine.
There's some other...

54
00:05:04,915 --> 00:05:07,626
There's a rock. That's mud.
That's just mud. There's a rock!

55
00:05:07,918 --> 00:05:13,136
That's my rock. That's my rock. Nobody touches my
rock. There's another rock. Two rocks. Three rocks.

56
00:05:13,452 --> 00:05:15,717
Peace rock!
Peace rock!

57
00:05:16,217 --> 00:05:19,011
It's the truce, the water truce!

58
00:05:19,949 --> 00:05:21,219
It's the water truce!

59
00:05:23,182 --> 00:05:27,185
It had been many, many years
since the peace rock was revealed...

60
00:05:27,686 --> 00:05:29,729
And the water truce was called.

61
00:05:37,487 --> 00:05:39,572
Hunting in the riverbank was now forbidden...

62
00:05:39,822 --> 00:05:43,492
Because, by law of the jungle,
drinking comes before eating.

63
00:05:43,784 --> 00:05:47,120
So you could come to the
peace rock, on a day like this...

64
00:05:47,371 --> 00:05:49,581
And find all people. Side by side.

65
00:06:01,592 --> 00:06:03,135
- Don't forget.
- No hunting.

66
00:06:03,469 --> 00:06:06,138
- Playing only.
- Playing only. I got it, amma.

67
00:06:06,684 --> 00:06:10,713
And remember, not everyone here has
seen a man cub in the jungle before.

68
00:06:10,822 --> 00:06:12,449
So behave yourself.

69
00:06:12,484 --> 00:06:14,247
Ok, ok. Can I go now?

70
00:06:14,354 --> 00:06:15,480
Take the pups with you.

71
00:06:16,272 --> 00:06:18,316
- Wait for me!
- Come on Gray!

72
00:06:20,985 --> 00:06:22,153
Take a look at this guy.

73
00:06:22,528 --> 00:06:24,321
- Excuse me.
- Sorry.

74
00:06:25,447 --> 00:06:28,000
- He's walking on two legs.
- Don't stare.

75
00:06:31,745 --> 00:06:33,121
Everybody's here.

76
00:06:33,663 --> 00:06:34,914
Is that a peacock?

77
00:06:36,332 --> 00:06:40,044
- Ooh, a stick!
- No, that's my stick.

78
00:06:45,424 --> 00:06:48,480
Sorry. My bad. It's involuntary.

79
00:06:49,030 --> 00:06:50,607
I could pee on it.

80
00:06:50,722 --> 00:06:51,722
Watch yourself please.

81
00:06:52,097 --> 00:06:53,431
Dad, what is that?

82
00:06:53,890 --> 00:06:55,350
Think that's a man cub.

83
00:06:55,683 --> 00:06:57,727
What's a man cub doing here?

84
00:06:59,103 --> 00:07:02,314
- Woah, don't forget the truce.
- I know the law, bucks.

85
00:07:10,739 --> 00:07:11,990
What is that?

86
00:07:24,585 --> 00:07:26,628
- Weird.
- That's weird.

87
00:07:28,171 --> 00:07:29,464
Mowgli.

88
00:07:32,759 --> 00:07:35,094
What was the rule about your tricks?

89
00:07:36,262 --> 00:07:38,181
It's not the wolf way.

90
00:07:38,514 --> 00:07:39,849
No more tricks.

91
00:07:41,809 --> 00:07:45,979
Chin up little one. We'll
make you a fine wolf yet.

92
00:07:47,522 --> 00:07:50,775
What about me? Am I gonna be
a fine wolf? Look at me howl.

93
00:07:53,987 --> 00:07:56,364
In some packs, the runt gets eaten.

94
00:08:12,921 --> 00:08:14,506
Mowgli, behind me.

95
00:08:18,426 --> 00:08:19,969
Don't leave my side.

96
00:09:05,302 --> 00:09:09,347
Everyone comes to peace rock,
so many smells to catch up on.

97
00:09:20,524 --> 00:09:25,863
I can't help but notice
there's this strange odor today.

98
00:09:27,739 --> 00:09:31,284
What is it? This scent that I'm on.

99
00:09:33,787 --> 00:09:40,001
I almost... almost think
it was some kind of man cub.

100
00:09:41,961 --> 00:09:45,380
Mowgli belongs to my pack, Shere Khan.

101
00:09:45,798 --> 00:09:49,801
Mowgli? They've given it a name.

102
00:09:51,136 --> 00:09:55,181
When was it we came to
adopt man into the jungle?

103
00:09:55,515 --> 00:09:56,808
He's just a cub.

104
00:09:57,308 --> 00:10:01,729
Does my face not remind you
of what a grown man can do?

105
00:10:04,481 --> 00:10:09,861
Shift your hunting ground for a few
years and everyone forgets how the law works.

106
00:10:10,904 --> 00:10:14,782
Well, let me remind you.
A man cub becomes man.

107
00:10:15,033 --> 00:10:17,660
And man is forbidden!

108
00:10:19,704 --> 00:10:22,214
- What do you know about law?
- Raksha.

109
00:10:22,326 --> 00:10:25,198
Hunting for pleasure,
killing for power.

110
00:10:25,199 --> 00:10:26,293
You've never known law.

111
00:10:26,543 --> 00:10:31,464
The cub is mine. Mine to me. So go back
to where you came from, you burned beast!

112
00:10:34,968 --> 00:10:37,637
The tiger knows who rules this part of the jungle.

113
00:10:38,054 --> 00:10:41,140
I'm sure he doesn't mean to
come here and make threats.

114
00:10:41,974 --> 00:10:44,435
Especially during a water truce.

115
00:10:52,859 --> 00:10:57,071
Know I'm deeply respectful of
these laws that keep us safe.

116
00:10:57,989 --> 00:11:02,368
So here's my promise.
Nothing lasts forever.

117
00:11:03,661 --> 00:11:08,957
The rains will return and the river
will rise. And when this rock disappears...

118
00:11:09,166 --> 00:11:10,750
That truce will end.

119
00:11:12,919 --> 00:11:17,673
You want to protect him?
Fine. But ask yourselves:

120
00:11:17,924 --> 00:11:21,469
How many lives is a man cub worth?

121
00:11:36,107 --> 00:11:37,525
How many lives?

122
00:11:39,986 --> 00:11:42,112
Who could answer that question?

123
00:12:11,097 --> 00:12:14,350
- The rain!
- Rain!

124
00:12:15,560 --> 00:12:22,000
Keep it dry, keep it dry, keep it dry.
These quills get stuck on everything!

125
00:12:24,276 --> 00:12:25,986
When the rains returned...

126
00:12:27,112 --> 00:12:29,614
there was a question
the council had to face.

127
00:12:55,305 --> 00:12:57,682
They deliberated and they argued.

128
00:12:58,015 --> 00:12:59,350
For many days.

129
00:13:05,064 --> 00:13:07,107
What do you think
they're talking about?

130
00:13:09,317 --> 00:13:12,028
No one had ever come
between the pack before.

131
00:13:13,363 --> 00:13:17,533
But Shere Khan's threat
was not to be ignored.

132
00:13:25,874 --> 00:13:28,502
Mowgli, you're not
supposed to go up there!

133
00:13:45,309 --> 00:13:46,518
Please!

134
00:13:48,186 --> 00:13:49,604
I am leaving.

135
00:13:51,982 --> 00:13:54,317
I don't wanna see anyone get hurt.

136
00:13:54,859 --> 00:13:56,569
Mowgli, go back to the den!

137
00:13:56,861 --> 00:13:58,661
A man cub belongs with man.

138
00:13:58,779 --> 00:14:01,532
- We raised him as one of our own.
- He'll have the boy either way.

139
00:14:01,824 --> 00:14:02,992
Akela.

140
00:14:05,285 --> 00:14:06,995
Maybe I can be of help.

141
00:14:07,412 --> 00:14:11,124
The boy's right. Maybe it's
time he found another people.

142
00:14:11,333 --> 00:14:13,626
- No.
- I am the one who brought him to you...

143
00:14:13,877 --> 00:14:16,004
And now I'll return
him to where he belongs.

144
00:14:16,254 --> 00:14:18,548
I won't let you.
He's my cub!

145
00:14:18,798 --> 00:14:20,299
We knew this day would come.

146
00:14:20,591 --> 00:14:22,968
We are the only
family he's ever known.

147
00:14:23,219 --> 00:14:27,973
Raksha, it's the only
place he'll be safe.

148
00:14:33,520 --> 00:14:36,105
It's okay, ammi. I won't go far.

149
00:14:36,606 --> 00:14:38,316
I'll come back and visit.

150
00:14:40,359 --> 00:14:42,528
Never forget this.

151
00:14:43,362 --> 00:14:47,199
You're mine. Mine to me.

152
00:14:47,658 --> 00:14:51,328
No matter where you go
or what they may call you...

153
00:14:51,578 --> 00:14:54,289
You will always be my son.

154
00:15:32,574 --> 00:15:36,744
I wish I could tell you that the
wolves could've fought Shere Khan.

155
00:15:38,454 --> 00:15:40,539
But this is not that kind of a tale.

156
00:15:42,917 --> 00:15:44,251
The turtles like me.

157
00:15:44,835 --> 00:15:46,420
Maybe the crocodiles.

158
00:15:47,170 --> 00:15:50,382
What about the rhinos?
They always let me hang around.

159
00:15:51,383 --> 00:15:53,679
Of course, the
rhinos sleep standing up.

160
00:15:55,261 --> 00:15:57,430
I don't think I'd
be very good at that.

161
00:15:57,680 --> 00:15:59,932
It's either the
turtles or the crocodiles.

162
00:16:00,224 --> 00:16:01,684
Which one do you think is better?

163
00:16:01,892 --> 00:16:02,935
Neither.

164
00:16:03,269 --> 00:16:04,436
What do you mean?

165
00:16:05,062 --> 00:16:06,897
I'm bringing you to the man village.

166
00:16:08,774 --> 00:16:10,025
What?

167
00:16:10,442 --> 00:16:12,277
Bagheera, I don't know man.

168
00:16:12,694 --> 00:16:13,778
You will.

169
00:16:15,863 --> 00:16:19,408
You always said we're not
supposed to go near a man village.

170
00:16:19,867 --> 00:16:20,910
That was different.

171
00:16:21,827 --> 00:16:25,456
Why is it different? You always
said stay away from the man village...

172
00:16:25,664 --> 00:16:29,835
Because you might fall in a trap or
get eaten or get hurt by flying rocks.

173
00:16:30,127 --> 00:16:31,211
I know what I said.

174
00:16:37,967 --> 00:16:39,468
Elephants.

175
00:16:40,177 --> 00:16:41,595
- Bow your head.
- Why?

176
00:16:42,471 --> 00:16:43,973
Show them respect.

177
00:16:45,099 --> 00:16:47,142
The elephants created this jungle.

178
00:16:47,893 --> 00:16:50,896
Where they've made furrows
with their tusks, the rivers ran.

179
00:16:51,313 --> 00:16:53,857
Where they blew with
their trunks, the leaves fell.

180
00:16:54,107 --> 00:16:58,653
They made all that belongs. The
mountains. The trees. The birds in the tree.

181
00:16:59,820 --> 00:17:03,866
But they didn't make you.
That is why you must go.

182
00:17:32,684 --> 00:17:34,811
- What if I live with the nilgai?
- No.

183
00:17:35,603 --> 00:17:36,646
Or the mongoose?

184
00:17:36,896 --> 00:17:38,439
This is not a discussion.

185
00:17:38,689 --> 00:17:41,358
But this is my home. I
don't even know what man's like.

186
00:17:41,692 --> 00:17:42,735
You'll learn.

187
00:17:43,027 --> 00:17:45,863
But I wanna stay in the
jungle. Why do I have to go there?

188
00:17:46,155 --> 00:17:50,492
Because the jungle is no longer safe
for you. You're being hunted by a tiger.

189
00:17:51,117 --> 00:17:53,161
Only man can protect you now.

190
00:17:55,496 --> 00:17:57,957
This isn't fair. You're
not giving me a choice.

191
00:17:58,249 --> 00:18:01,419
There's a lot of stuff you're not
telling me too. Don't think I didn't notice.

192
00:18:01,794 --> 00:18:03,391
You say you're taking
me where I came from...

193
00:18:03,403 --> 00:18:04,797
But you found me in the jungle.

194
00:18:05,089 --> 00:18:07,341
Are you bringing me
back to the jungle? No.

195
00:18:07,633 --> 00:18:10,594
Why are you bringing me to the man
village if you found me in the jungle?

196
00:18:10,802 --> 00:18:12,554
And why does that
tiger hate me so much?

197
00:18:12,895 --> 00:18:15,157
Does he know me? Sure
seems like he knows me.

198
00:18:15,261 --> 00:18:16,261
Down.

199
00:18:17,100 --> 00:18:19,340
What? Now we have to
bow to the buffalo too?

200
00:18:19,894 --> 00:18:23,397
Listen to me. This is not a game.
You're gonna run to that ravine.

201
00:18:24,148 --> 00:18:25,649
What are you talking about?

202
00:18:25,941 --> 00:18:29,101
Go to the North where the sky glows
at night. I'll find you on that path.

203
00:18:29,319 --> 00:18:31,321
Bagheera, I'm not taking one more step -

204
00:18:58,679 --> 00:18:59,972
Run, Mowgli!

205
00:19:02,308 --> 00:19:03,309
Run!

206
00:20:36,644 --> 00:20:39,814
Gray, what's wrong? Why
don't you come outside and play?

207
00:20:41,649 --> 00:20:42,858
What is that?

208
00:20:47,195 --> 00:20:48,989
Why did he have to leave?

209
00:20:49,239 --> 00:20:50,323
Gray.

210
00:20:50,615 --> 00:20:53,910
We could have protected him.
We shouldn't have let him go.

211
00:20:54,494 --> 00:20:58,623
I miss him too. What's
important is he's safe now.

212
00:21:07,200 --> 00:21:08,200
Get inside.

213
00:21:54,337 --> 00:21:56,384
I suppose you know why I've come.

214
00:21:59,470 --> 00:22:01,430
The man cub has left the jungle.

215
00:22:06,310 --> 00:22:09,938
I thought I made myself clear,
I wanted him turned over to me.

216
00:22:11,314 --> 00:22:12,816
We no longer harbor him.

217
00:22:13,817 --> 00:22:15,693
He has left the pack.

218
00:22:16,944 --> 00:22:19,488
And where, may I ask, has he gone?

219
00:22:24,243 --> 00:22:26,161
He is with his own kind now.

220
00:22:28,455 --> 00:22:30,665
So the man cub has left the jungle.

221
00:22:31,583 --> 00:22:32,834
That's right.

222
00:22:33,334 --> 00:22:35,586
You and I no longer have a quarrel.

223
00:22:35,878 --> 00:22:39,131
And, most importantly, we have peace.

224
00:22:45,804 --> 00:22:47,681
Well, I guess it's done then.

225
00:22:49,224 --> 00:22:52,493
Unless I can draw him back out!

226
00:22:53,377 --> 00:22:54,489
Akela!

227
00:22:57,523 --> 00:22:59,525
Have I got your attention now?

228
00:23:00,234 --> 00:23:04,405
I didn't want it to be
this way. I made it so simple.

229
00:23:05,197 --> 00:23:08,950
All I asked for was one
thing and you denied me.

230
00:23:09,201 --> 00:23:13,204
Well, that ends
now. Spread the word.

231
00:23:13,872 --> 00:23:17,750
Until I have the man cub,
these hills are my hills.

232
00:23:18,338 --> 00:23:20,346
You did not respond to reason.

233
00:23:21,268 --> 00:23:22,852
So now you will know fear.

234
00:26:12,105 --> 00:26:13,309
Bagheera.

235
00:27:58,438 --> 00:27:59,534
Hey there!

236
00:28:03,726 --> 00:28:05,060
Do you have a language?

237
00:28:09,217 --> 00:28:10,555
You're kinda cute, I guess.

238
00:28:12,629 --> 00:28:13,906
You wanna bite?

239
00:28:16,520 --> 00:28:18,261
Come on. Come here.

240
00:28:18,348 --> 00:28:19,459
Come on. It's all right.

241
00:28:20,335 --> 00:28:21,756
Don't be afraid.

242
00:28:31,015 --> 00:28:32,015
Come on.

243
00:28:34,040 --> 00:28:35,966
Hey, those are mine!

244
00:28:39,194 --> 00:28:40,353
Hey, come back!

245
00:28:42,833 --> 00:28:44,145
Hey, those are mine!

246
00:28:46,845 --> 00:28:47,963
Drop it!

247
00:29:04,783 --> 00:29:05,783
Hello?

