? And then maybe try a few. ?

493
00:49:39,430 --> 00:49:41,977
? The bear necessities of
life, they'll come to you. ?

494
00:49:42,907 --> 00:49:44,697
? They will come to you! ?

495
00:49:45,439 --> 00:49:47,004
? Yeah, they'll come to you! ?

496
00:49:47,989 --> 00:49:48,463
? Come to you. ?

497
00:49:48,538 --> 00:49:51,503
Baloo, Baloo,
Baloo. Look.

498
00:49:55,006 --> 00:49:56,382
Stay low on my back.

499
00:50:04,640 --> 00:50:05,849
Come on out and show yourself.

500
00:50:13,565 --> 00:50:14,566
Bagheera!

501
00:50:16,526 --> 00:50:17,526
Mowgli.

502
00:50:18,488 --> 00:50:22,012
Oh, I was looking everywhere
for you. I thought you were gone.

503
00:50:22,114 --> 00:50:22,738
Are you alright?

504
00:50:22,750 --> 00:50:24,658
Yeah, I can't believe you found me.

505
00:50:24,700 --> 00:50:26,652
I was so worried about you.

506
00:50:26,741 --> 00:50:30,887
I was lost, and I didn't know what happened.
But then I met Baloo. And then he saved me...

507
00:50:30,978 --> 00:50:34,359
From a giant snake. And
now we're working together!

508
00:50:34,445 --> 00:50:38,487
Really? That's a new wrinkle.
I didn't know soft bears worked.

509
00:50:39,212 --> 00:50:40,631
Come on Mowgli, let's be on our way.

510
00:50:42,299 --> 00:50:43,299
Wait!

511
00:50:44,510 --> 00:50:46,842
Yeah, go on ahead. I'll catch up.

512
00:50:47,846 --> 00:50:49,450
Don't be mad, ok?

513
00:50:49,848 --> 00:50:50,815
Why would I be mad?

514
00:50:50,899 --> 00:50:52,439
'Cause you're always mad when I do stuff.

515
00:50:52,545 --> 00:50:54,638
You gotta promise not to be mad this time.

516
00:50:54,852 --> 00:50:56,687
Show me, then I'll decide.

517
00:50:57,438 --> 00:50:58,439
Come on, check it out!

518
00:51:02,067 --> 00:51:07,363
These are vines I use on the cliff. I twirl
them together to make them longer and stronger.

519
00:51:07,499 --> 00:51:09,156
See how strong they are?

520
00:51:10,902 --> 00:51:12,327
You wanna see the really cool part?

521
00:51:12,952 --> 00:51:14,495
It's inside. Come on, let's go!

522
00:51:16,372 --> 00:51:17,372
Come on!

523
00:51:28,425 --> 00:51:30,135
It's the honey stash for winter!

524
00:51:32,303 --> 00:51:33,930
Have you lost your mind?!

525
00:51:35,682 --> 00:51:37,058
You said you wouldn't get mad.

526
00:51:37,683 --> 00:51:40,137
Did you listen to
anything Akela taught you?

527
00:51:40,239 --> 00:51:42,541
There's no place in
the jungle for these...

528
00:51:43,147 --> 00:51:45,858
Tricks. You want to do this,
you do this in the man village.

529
00:51:46,733 --> 00:51:49,027
But I'm helping Baloo
get ready for hibernation.

530
00:51:49,361 --> 00:51:52,739
Bears don't hibernate in the
jungle. What are you teaching him?

531
00:51:53,781 --> 00:51:56,576
Not full hibernation, but I nap. A lot.

532
00:51:57,076 --> 00:51:59,153
Listen to me, you con artist.

533
00:51:59,711 --> 00:52:02,680
He may not know your game,
but I do. He's leaving now.

534
00:52:02,715 --> 00:52:04,708
- But I don't wanna leave!
- You don't have a choice!

535
00:52:06,543 --> 00:52:09,063
Why don't we all just settle down
for a minute? Look, it's gotten late...

536
00:52:09,379 --> 00:52:12,048
Too late to travel. So why don't
we all just have a little honey?

537
00:52:12,090 --> 00:52:15,593
- I don't eat honey.
- No problem. I'll eat the honey.

538
00:52:16,427 --> 00:52:19,388
Let's all get a good night's sleep and
we can talk about this in the morning?

539
00:52:20,639 --> 00:52:21,599
Fine.

540
00:52:21,640 --> 00:52:23,434
But we're leaving first thing.

541
00:54:40,897 --> 00:54:41,897
Mowgli.

542
00:54:50,777 --> 00:54:51,777
Where is he?

543
00:54:52,487 --> 00:54:54,491
- In the pit.
- In the what?

544
00:54:54,571 --> 00:54:55,636
Is this your teaching?

545
00:54:55,657 --> 00:54:58,409
Oh, come on. You know I'd never
teach him to mess around with elephants.

546
00:55:53,543 --> 00:55:54,543
Hey guys.

547
00:56:05,262 --> 00:56:06,972
What'd I tell ya? He's special.

548
00:56:08,432 --> 00:56:10,517
I know he's special. I raised him.

549
00:56:13,728 --> 00:56:17,231
Then don't make him leave,
Bagheera. You gotta let him be what he is.

550
00:56:18,065 --> 00:56:22,528
- You don't understand. The boy is in danger.
- I know. He told me. He's being hunted...

551
00:56:22,570 --> 00:56:23,202
By a tiger.

552
00:56:23,237 --> 00:56:25,781
Not any tiger. Shere Khan.

553
00:56:26,198 --> 00:56:27,407
Shere Khan's hunting him?

554
00:56:30,243 --> 00:56:34,233
But if you send him back to the man village,
they'll ruin him. They'll make a man out of him.

555
00:56:35,029 --> 00:56:36,638
We should send him back to the wolf pack.

556
00:56:36,673 --> 00:56:38,501
Who's their alpha?
Akela? He can protect him.

557
00:56:39,210 --> 00:56:40,753
Akela is dead.

558
00:56:41,670 --> 00:56:43,672
- What?
- Shere Khan killed him.

559
00:56:44,339 --> 00:56:48,406
He will stop at nothing
until he has this boy, nothing.

560
00:56:48,829 --> 00:56:52,222
The only way we can save him
is if he goes to that man village.

561
00:56:53,014 --> 00:56:54,265
Please, Baloo?

562
00:56:55,308 --> 00:56:57,143
You are the only he'll listen to.

563
00:57:25,544 --> 00:57:27,045
- Hey kid.
- Hey.

564
00:57:28,922 --> 00:57:30,548
That was pretty cool,
what you did back there.

565
00:57:32,092 --> 00:57:33,624
Bagheera didn't think so.

566
00:57:33,636 --> 00:57:36,367
Oh no, I talked to
him. He was very impressed.

567
00:57:37,972 --> 00:57:40,500
- He was?
- We both were. Yeah.

568
00:57:40,891 --> 00:57:44,500
I- I've never seen anyone get
that close to an elephant before.

569
00:57:50,734 --> 00:57:53,784
So, listen kid, I gotta
talk to you about something.

570
00:57:54,320 --> 00:57:55,363
What do you wanna talk about?

571
00:57:55,822 --> 00:57:57,240
Well, you know, I've been thinking.

572
00:57:57,615 --> 00:58:04,000
Now that your friend has shown up, maybe
it's time for you two to just mosey along.

573
00:58:06,790 --> 00:58:08,270
Ya know, now it's winter and...

574
00:58:09,042 --> 00:58:10,710
And it's really time for you to go.

575
00:58:11,670 --> 00:58:13,046
But I wanna stay here with you.

576
00:58:15,590 --> 00:58:16,841
We're buddies, aren't we?

577
00:58:18,000 --> 00:58:23,293
Huh? No. We were never friends. I
certainly never thought of you as my friend.

578
00:58:23,419 --> 00:58:27,104
I mean, you helped me get honey and
I don't really need you anymore but...

579
00:58:30,228 --> 00:58:32,022
Do I have to spell this out?

580
00:58:34,357 --> 00:58:36,567
I don't want you around anymore.

581
00:58:50,038 --> 00:58:51,038
Well, I did it.

582
00:58:52,749 --> 00:58:54,500
And that's about the
hardest thing I've ever done.

583
00:58:57,211 --> 00:58:58,211
I know.

584
00:59:43,671 --> 00:59:44,671
Go away.

585
00:59:50,844 --> 00:59:51,844
Get away from me.

586
00:59:56,307 --> 00:59:57,391
Stop it!

587
01:00:05,941 --> 01:00:07,025
Get away from me!

588
01:00:13,323 --> 01:00:14,323
Mowgli!

589
01:00:27,586 --> 01:00:29,004
Mowgli! Hold on!

590
01:00:33,174 --> 01:00:34,174
Bagheera!

591
01:00:37,178 --> 01:00:38,989
What was that? Where
are they taking him?

592
01:00:39,069 --> 01:00:40,069
This way.

593
01:00:51,347 --> 01:00:54,902
We see you, we see you!

594
01:01:03,536 --> 01:01:06,205
Come on, jump!
And watch the claws.

595
01:01:17,089 --> 01:01:19,008
Help!

596
01:01:22,678 --> 01:01:23,678
Help!

597
01:02:12,300 --> 01:02:15,065
- Uh...
- I'll take it from here.

598
01:02:15,393 --> 01:02:17,603
No. I'm- I'm coming.

599
01:02:18,312 --> 01:02:22,109
It- It's doable if
I don't have to go too high.

600
01:02:22,274 --> 01:02:23,525
Good. Let's get going.

601
01:02:24,693 --> 01:02:25,693
Alright.

602
01:03:10,860 --> 01:03:14,228
A bird, that can't be a good sign.

603
01:03:14,342 --> 01:03:18,000
Baloo, look at me.
Look at nothing but me.

604
01:03:18,743 --> 01:03:24,373
- You're doing fine. Just keep your eyes up. High.
- Alright. I'm coming, I'm coming.

605
01:04:57,041 --> 01:04:59,001
What part of the jungle you from?

606
01:05:02,296 --> 01:05:06,634
You, man cub. You come from the South or North?

607
01:05:06,751 --> 01:05:09,471
What- What part of the- the- the jungle?

608
01:05:10,571 --> 01:05:12,194
The South, I guess?

609
01:05:13,556 --> 01:05:19,395
Sodom jungle. The Seeonee. Beautiful,
I hear. I- I never been there myself.

610
01:05:20,271 --> 01:05:27,027
So, tell me, you ever had a taste of
the pawpaw fruit down there in the Seeonee?

611
01:05:27,778 --> 01:05:30,908
Some people call it, uh,
what's the word? Papaya.

612
01:05:31,002 --> 01:05:33,443
Stolen words. I say pawpaw...

613
01:05:33,530 --> 01:05:37,128
'Cause of the sound it makes
when it tumbles to the jungle floor.

614
01:05:38,663 --> 01:05:40,164
Try it!

615
01:05:45,377 --> 01:05:47,295
Go ahead.

616
01:05:54,719 --> 01:05:56,929
It's good.

617
01:05:58,524 --> 01:05:59,817
You know who I am?

618
01:06:01,285 --> 01:06:01,999
No.

619
01:06:02,309 --> 01:06:05,312
I am the king of the Bandar-log.

620
01:06:08,857 --> 01:06:09,858
Call me Louie.

621
01:06:20,284 --> 01:06:21,744
I did it.

622
01:06:22,077 --> 01:06:24,621
Well done, old chap.

623
01:06:26,039 --> 01:06:28,166
He must be in there.

624
01:06:28,542 --> 01:06:29,668
Follow me.

625
01:06:30,001 --> 01:06:33,113
No, no. We're on level ground here.

626
01:06:33,209 --> 01:06:36,007
I'm in charge and I've got a plan.

627
01:06:37,258 --> 01:06:41,345
And you are a man club who
wants to live in the jungle?

628
01:06:42,012 --> 01:06:43,597
How do you know that?

629
01:06:43,931 --> 01:06:49,436
Kid, I got ears. My ears got
ears. You wanna live here...

630
01:06:49,936 --> 01:06:52,856
You'll need a
people to protect you.

631
01:06:53,273 --> 01:06:57,235
Only I can protect you,
and I will for a price.

632
01:06:57,568 --> 01:07:00,529
I don't have anything to give you.

633
01:07:01,530 --> 01:07:04,074
I think you do.

634
01:07:04,867 --> 01:07:06,535
What?

635
01:07:07,244 --> 01:07:08,995
Look around, man cub.

636
01:07:09,496 --> 01:07:16,544
I got everything. I have plentiful food,
endless treasure, command vast legions.

637
01:07:16,919 --> 01:07:22,132
But there's one thing I don't have
and that's the one thing you can give me.

638
01:07:23,592 --> 01:07:25,928
The red flower.

639
01:07:27,095 --> 01:07:28,930
I don't have that.

640
01:07:29,764 --> 01:07:32,100
You're a man, aren't you?

641
01:07:32,809 --> 01:07:38,773
That's what makes you a man. You can
summon your red flower and control it.

642
01:07:39,273 --> 01:07:42,067
They told me not to go near the red flower.

643
01:07:42,568 --> 01:07:44,342
You know why they tell you that?

644
01:07:44,354 --> 01:07:46,363
Because once you have it, you rise...

645
01:07:46,738 --> 01:07:54,287
To the top of the food chain. Nothing in
this jungle can stand up to the red flower.

646
01:07:56,122 --> 01:07:59,375
Please, I just wanna go.

647
01:08:01,961 --> 01:08:05,088
? Now don't try to kid me, man cub. ?

648
01:08:05,631 --> 01:08:07,224
? I'll make a deal with you. ?

649
01:08:07,349 --> 01:08:11,344
? What I desire is man's red
fire to make my dream come true. ?

650
01:08:12,011 --> 01:08:14,597
? Now gimme the secret, man cub. Come on! ?

651
01:08:15,223 --> 01:08:20,478
? Clue me what to do. Give me the power
of man's red flower so I can be like you. ?

652
01:08:22,605 --> 01:08:25,023
? I wanna be like you-oo-oo. ?

653
01:08:25,691 --> 01:08:29,611
? I wanna walk like you,
talk like you too-oo-oo ?

654
01:08:29,736 --> 01:08:39,500
? You see, it's true-oo-oo. Someone like
me-ee-ee can learn to be like someone like you-oo-oo ?>/i>

655
01:08:40,287 --> 01:08:44,708
? Now you might think it's
ridiculous that me, a gigantopithecus ?

656
01:08:45,250 --> 01:08:49,212
? Would ever dream, I'd like to
team with the likes of you man cub. ?

657
01:08:49,880 --> 01:08:53,800
? But together, we'd have powers.
All the jungle's treasure, ours. ?

658
01:08:54,300 --> 01:08:58,429
? I got desire. You got the fire.
But the dream I dream takes two. ?

659
01:09:00,389 --> 01:09:02,891
? I wanna be like you-oo-oo ?

660
01:09:03,600 --> 01:09:07,604
? I wanna use that flame
just the same as you can do. ?

661
01:09:08,397 --> 01:09:10,440
? Oh, how magnificus it would be! ?

662
01:09:11,066 --> 01:09:16,654
? A gigantopithecus like me could
learn to do like you humans do-oo-oo ?

663
01:09:18,572 --> 01:09:22,618
Just one thing we need
to reach our full potential.

664
01:09:23,077 --> 01:09:25,370
Bring me that red flower.

665
01:09:25,871 --> 01:09:32,168
And when we rule this jungle, I will protect
you and you will want for nothing ever again.

666
01:09:32,752 --> 01:09:33,920
I can't!

667
01:09:34,295 --> 01:09:36,172
You can't or you won't?

668
01:09:36,506 --> 01:09:37,632
I can't!

669
01:09:38,132 --> 01:09:39,508
You will!

670
01:09:39,967 --> 01:09:41,385
Excuse me!

671
01:09:41,677 --> 01:09:43,470
Anybody?

672
01:09:44,513 --> 01:09:47,891
Excuse me. Am I in the right monkey temple?

673
01:09:48,812 --> 01:09:53,021
Oh my gosh, is that King Louie?

674
01:09:53,942 --> 01:09:55,644
This is so exciting.

675
01:09:56,057 --> 01:10:03,033
The legends do you no justice,
sir. You are truly enormous!

676
01:10:04,198 --> 01:10:12,198
In the best way, look at all of that flesh
just squatting there on an ancient throne.

677
01:10:12,850 --> 01:10:14,300
How- how- how majestic.

678
01:10:14,944 --> 01:10:16,334
Seize him!

679
01:10:16,709 --> 01:10:20,046
Hey, hang on! Can you hang
on? Can you just hang on?

680
01:10:20,588 --> 01:10:25,781
I climbed a mountain to see you, and I'm
not a climber, just to be in your presence.

681
01:10:25,897 --> 01:10:28,000
For me, this is a dream come true.

682
01:10:28,720 --> 01:10:30,764
Throw him off the cliff!

683
01:10:31,181 --> 01:10:36,023
Wait, wait, wait. I
have no problem with that.

684
01:10:36,135 --> 01:10:37,623
I don't have any problem with that.

685
01:10:37,734 --> 01:10:42,000
I came up here without an
invitation. Extremely presumptious of me.

686
01:10:42,549 --> 01:10:45,474
Let me interrupt myself. I just
gotta say, you guys are so much...

687
01:10:45,546 --> 01:10:47,696
Handsomer in person than anyone knows.

688
01:10:48,155 --> 01:10:49,528
No one ever gets up close to you.

689
01:10:49,618 --> 01:10:54,202
I guess that's why. Because of the
smell. I mean, the smell is- is- is rough.

690
01:10:54,869 --> 01:10:58,800
But, it's not just, "Oh, look
at me!" It's, "I got the brains."

691
01:10:59,299 --> 01:11:01,542
You guys got the- the
know how. You got the noggin.

692
01:11:02,418 --> 01:11:05,917
You came up with this stuff, with the
thumb. Come on, show me. How do you do that?

693
01:11:06,001 --> 01:11:09,900
I can't do that. Look. I scratch,
I rub. You know, I can grab a fish.

694
01:11:10,513 --> 01:11:14,427
But I was hoping, and you may not be
open to this at all, but I was hoping...

695
01:11:14,487 --> 01:11:20,267
And once again, it's a dream, but I was
hoping that I might become a Bandar-log myself.

696
01:11:20,768 --> 01:11:24,438
Gosh, I wanna be like you. I
am hitching my wagon to your star.

697
01:11:29,105 --> 01:11:30,889
No one leaves!

698
01:11:30,924 --> 01:11:33,571
I can show myself
out, thanks! Goodbye!

699
01:11:50,921 --> 01:11:52,823
We'll try to hold them off.

700
01:12:28,207 --> 01:12:30,054
Where you going man cub?

701
01:12:30,548 --> 01:12:31,548
Stay away from me!

702
01:12:32,223 --> 01:12:36,311
You don't have anyone
now. I'm your only hope.

703
01:12:36,384 --> 01:12:39,791
I can make it real good for
you here. Where else you gonna go?

704
01:12:39,876 --> 01:12:42,885
I'll go back to the pack.
I'll go back to Akela!

705
01:12:43,552 --> 01:12:48,288
Akela? Oh, you didn't hear?

706
01:12:49,586 --> 01:12:52,227
Shere Khan killed him.

707
01:12:54,249 --> 01:12:56,298
Must have been on account of you.

708
01:12:56,939 --> 01:12:59,358
No, you're lying!

709
01:13:03,674 --> 01:13:05,344
Don't run away...

710
01:13:08,075 --> 01:13:10,702
From who you are, ya hear me?!

711
01:13:37,068 --> 01:13:40,479
Think about it, man cub.

712
01:13:43,137 --> 01:13:45,690
We can rule this jungle.

713
01:13:49,342 --> 01:13:51,043
Listen to reason.

714
01:14:07,022 --> 01:14:08,255
Gotcha!

715
01:14:50,725 --> 01:14:51,787
Mowgli!

716
01:15:16,192 --> 01:15:21,155
If anything happens to that
kid, I'll never forgive myself.

717
01:15:21,572 --> 01:15:22,596
Bagheera!

718
01:15:22,727 --> 01:15:23,727
Mowgli?

719
01:15:24,918 --> 01:15:27,438
Stay there! We'll come around to you!

720
01:15:29,969 --> 01:15:30,969
Is it true?!

721
01:15:31,081 --> 01:15:32,582
What?

722
01:15:32,999 --> 01:15:34,659
Is Akela dead?!

723
01:15:36,602 --> 01:15:38,546
We were going to tell you.

724
01:15:38,921 --> 01:15:44,468
You knew! You both knew! And
nobody did anything about it!

725
01:15:44,760 --> 01:15:46,470
Kid, just hold on!

726
01:15:47,054 --> 01:15:49,097
Someone's gotta do something!

727
01:15:49,389 --> 01:15:51,266
Mowgli!

728
01:18:09,035 --> 01:18:12,353
There's no trace of him!
Where could he have gone?

729
01:18:26,617 --> 01:18:28,243
Come on!

730
01:18:49,763 --> 01:18:53,183
It's man! He's come to the jungle!

731
01:18:58,934 --> 01:19:02,358
- Ammi, what's happenin'?
- The red flower.

732
01:19:02,608 --> 01:19:05,569
Everybody, get to the river!

733
01:19:18,331 --> 01:19:20,499
Red flower, red flower, red flower!

734
01:19:22,006 --> 01:19:23,953
Pups, come on! Stay close!

735
01:19:37,828 --> 01:19:40,976
Is that Mowgli?

736
01:19:43,958 --> 01:19:45,196
Shere Khan!

737
01:19:46,523 --> 01:19:49,151
Shere Khan! I'm not afraid of you!

738
01:19:50,107 --> 01:19:52,288
No one has to be afraid of you anymore!

739
01:19:56,841 --> 01:19:57,841
No.

740
01:20:01,480 --> 01:20:05,040
I think they're afraid
of something else now.

741
01:20:20,644 --> 01:20:23,032
The man cub is now a man.

742
01:20:26,411 --> 01:20:28,228
Gray.

743
01:20:31,252 --> 01:20:35,624
Always a proud day
when they come of age.

744
01:20:38,533 --> 01:20:42,533
You can fool them,
but you can't fool me.

745
01:20:42,616 --> 01:20:46,078
I'm the one who saw your future.

746
01:20:46,453 --> 01:20:48,843
I saw what you'd become.

747
01:20:54,740 --> 01:21:00,316
Come now. Use the red flower.
Use it on me like your father did!

748
01:21:04,188 --> 01:21:06,863
Show everyone what you really are!

749
01:21:12,528 --> 01:21:16,189
I am Mowgli of the
Seeonee and this is my home!

750
01:21:21,911 --> 01:21:24,175
That was the stupidest
thing you could have done.

751
01:21:25,543 --> 01:21:33,543
And now, you have nothing. No
claws, no fur, no teeth. And no friends.

752
01:21:36,622 --> 01:21:41,128
This is the law of the jungle.
As old and as true as the sky.

753
01:21:41,865 --> 01:21:42,611
What is this?

754
01:21:42,746 --> 01:21:45,353
The wolf that keeps it may prosper.

755
01:21:45,454 --> 01:21:48,389
- But the wolf that breaks it will die.
- You fools.

756
01:21:48,510 --> 01:21:53,249
Like the creeper that girdles the
tree trunk, the law runneth over and back.

757
01:21:53,364 --> 01:21:58,541
Fine. Rise up, all of you! You want to
put yourselves between me and the man cub?

758
01:21:58,641 --> 01:22:03,317
- And the strength of the wolf is the pack!
- I'm going to have you all in my teeth!

759
01:22:27,022 --> 01:22:28,046
No!

760
01:22:28,171 --> 01:22:30,068
Wolves, attack!

761
01:22:35,311 --> 01:22:38,675
- Stay here!
- But I wanna fight with the wolves!

762
01:22:38,711 --> 01:22:40,971
You can't fight him like
a wolf, you're not a wolf.

763
01:22:42,283 --> 01:22:43,860
Fight him like a man.

764
01:22:46,342 --> 01:22:47,385
Now, go!

765
01:22:50,369 --> 01:22:51,651
We'll hold him off.

766
01:23:39,041 --> 01:23:41,509
It's time we put an end to this.

767
01:23:42,156 --> 01:23:43,490
No!

768
01:23:58,762 --> 01:24:00,339
Dead tree.

769
01:25:08,595 --> 01:25:10,270
It's just you and me now!

770
01:26:06,975 --> 01:26:08,707
Break, break!

771
01:26:58,754 --> 01:27:01,338
You've got nowhere to go, man cub!

772
01:27:39,392 --> 01:27:43,293
Did you think I would let you grow old?

773
01:27:51,303 --> 01:27:55,596
Either I'll devour you
or the red flower will.

774
01:27:56,601 --> 01:27:58,599
It's just a matter of time.

775
01:28:02,217 --> 01:28:06,940
How long did you really
think you'd survive against me?

776
01:28:07,441 --> 01:28:10,610
Longer than your father did?

777
01:28:11,820 --> 01:28:16,157
Longer than Akela?

778
01:28:32,050 --> 01:28:35,633
I'm not afraid of you!

779
01:28:41,199 --> 01:28:43,182
Do you hear me?

780
01:28:44,424 --> 01:28:47,644
I'm done running from you.

781
01:30:17,058 --> 01:30:20,813
You stood your ground, old
boy. You stood your gound.

782
01:30:36,093 --> 01:30:37,828
Ammi, ammi!

783
01:30:39,705 --> 01:30:42,041
My son.

784
01:30:42,042 --> 01:30:44,188
- Mowgli!
- It's Mowgli!

785
01:31:18,348 --> 01:31:20,486
Will you look at that.

786
01:31:31,330 --> 01:31:37,197
And where they made furrows in the
ground with their tusks, the rivers ran.

787
01:32:05,557 --> 01:32:09,800
In my years, I've seen a lot
in this jungle. But that night...

788
01:32:10,650 --> 01:32:13,291
I saw something I'll never forget.

789
01:32:14,101 --> 01:32:22,700
I saw a little boy, without a people, bring
all the jungle together for the very first time.

790
01:32:43,749 --> 01:32:46,405
- Just a few more turns.
- Going high!

791
01:32:46,822 --> 01:32:48,573
Stay low.

792
01:32:52,897 --> 01:32:54,579
He never listens.

793
01:33:03,983 --> 01:33:05,013
Gotcha!

794
01:33:05,172 --> 01:33:07,424
- Come on Mowgli!
- You went through the tree!

795
01:33:08,049 --> 01:33:10,135
You guys!

796
01:33:10,927 --> 01:33:14,472
Too fast! Anybody ever
teach you how to jog?!

797
01:33:15,098 --> 01:33:17,802
You went high when everyone
else stayed on the trail.

798
01:33:17,924 --> 01:33:18,924
But that's what you do.

799
01:33:18,996 --> 01:33:21,911
Maybe, but I'm not a wolf.
Next time, stay together!

800
01:33:21,991 --> 01:33:23,119
Come on guys!

801
01:33:24,085 --> 01:33:28,944
Where the strength of
the pack is the- is the...

802
01:33:29,778 --> 01:33:33,740
- And the strength of the wolf is the pack.
- Mowgli's back!

803
01:33:37,495 --> 01:33:39,769
Hey Mowgli, wait for us!

804
01:33:40,970 --> 01:33:42,924
- Hurry up guys.
- Hi Gray.

805
01:33:48,554 --> 01:33:51,089
Look well, wolves.

806
01:33:56,458 --> 01:34:01,307
- This is the law of the jungle...
- As old and as true as the sky.

807
01:34:02,057 --> 01:34:04,949
The wolf that keeps it may prosper...

808
01:34:05,049 --> 01:34:07,408
But the wolf that breaks it will die.

809
01:34:08,188 --> 01:34:10,815
And like the creeper
that girdles the tree trunks

810
01:34:11,483 --> 01:34:14,762
The law runneth over and back.
For the strength of the pack-

811
01:34:18,413 --> 01:34:22,451
- It is nice up here.
- Now he can climb.

812
01:34:25,627 --> 01:34:29,457
Please don't tell me
you're about to head down.

813
01:34:32,877 --> 01:34:35,254
Good.

814
01:34:37,988 --> 01:34:39,928
I could get used to this.